08/05/2011
ANKARA, Turkey -- UN Secretary-General Ban Ki-moon arrived in Turkey on Saturday (May 7th) to take part in the 4th UN Conference on the Least Developed Countries that kicks off in Istanbul on Monday.
While in Turkey, Ban will meet President Abdullah Gul and Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan.
The UN chief arrived in Turkey from Bulgaria, where he met Prime Minister Boyko Borissov, President Georgi Parvanov and other senior officials.
(Anadolu news agency, Zaman, World Bulletin - 07/05/11)
